                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Contends that the people of Natchez were not in support of secession and
                    questions the right of the Mississippi Convention to secede without the people's
                    consent. The Courier also questions the right of the Southern Confederacy to
                    appoint rulers, alter Constitutions and impose taxes without popular consent.</summary>
                <note/>
